Summarize this profile suitable for a keynote speaker or book author bio:

Ron F. Del Rosario is a widely recognized expert practitioner in securing modern artificial intelligence and machine learning (AI/ML) systems. He is a popular speaker at top international security conferences such as RSA, DefCon, and Black Hat. Ron has appeared on numerous podcasts and live events, sharing his insights on securing AI, Language Models, and Agents.

With nearly twenty years of experience in the Software as a Service (SaaS) industry, including involvement in Initial Public Offerings (IPOs) and Mergers and Acquisitions (M&A), Ron has refined his skills in creating high-reliability SaaS solutions.

Since 2018, he has been a pioneer in AI/ML security, developing internal frameworks for AI/ML security governance and AI Security Posture Management (AI-SPM), supported by a patent on using AI/ML for secure software development.

Ron’s strategic approach results in actionable initiatives. He works with business leaders and Chief Information Security Officers (CISOs) to promote the secure adoption of AI. His leadership and contributions to the Open Web Application Security Project (OWASP) Gen AI Security Project, along with his work on AI security books and papers, highlight his dedication to advancing the industry.

His current research focuses on the secure design, architecture, and cost-efficiency of Language Model (xLM) Agents deployment in enterprise environments. Ron partners with a wide range of AI security researchers from both private and government sectors, including prestigious academic institutions.

Presently, Ron is the Head of AI Security for SAP Intelligent Spend and Business Network (ISBN), where he plays a key role in fostering innovation at the crossroads of cybersecurity and AI.

Since 2018 he has pioneered AI/ML security frameworks, including the award‑winning AI Security Posture Management (AI‑SPM) system and a patent for using AI/ML to harden software development. His work on the OWASP Gen AI Security Project, as well as his numerous books and research papers, has set the standard for protecting language models and autonomous agents in enterprise environments.

Ron is a sought‑after keynote speaker, regularly appearing at RSA, DefCon, Black Hat, and other top security conferences. He also shares his insights on podcasts and live events worldwide.

Today he serves as Head of AI Security for SAP Intelligent Spend & Business Network (ISBN), where he drives innovation at the intersection of cybersecurity and AI, translating complex threat landscapes into actionable strategies for business leaders and CISOs.
